results.name: Number of strict planar branching factorizations of n.
comment: A strict planar branching factorization of n is either the number n itself or a sequence of at least two strict planar branching factorizations, one of each factor in a strict ordered factorization of n.
formula: a(product of n distinct primes) = A319122(n).
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 11 2018
